## {{ rule.title }}

{# IRS-VERIFIED 2026-05-12 — 2025 Form 1040 fields 33/34/35a/36/37 (payments + refund + amount owed block) against https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-pdf/f1040.pdf #}
After regular tax, FTC, and NIIT are settled, [Form 1040](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1040) lines 33-37 reconcile total tax against the year's payments. If estimated payments and withholding exceed total tax, line 34 is a **refund** (and you choose direct deposit on line 35a or carry-forward on line 36). If total tax exceeds payments, line 37 is the **amount owed**.

